# Project Structure

This project follows a standard Go project layout with React frontend.

## Directory Structure

```
.
├── cmd/                    # Main applications
│   └── server/            # Main server application
├── internal/              # Private application code
│   ├── api/              # API handlers and routes
│   ├── config/           # Configuration management
│   ├── models/           # Data models
│   └── services/         # Business logic
├── pkg/                   # Public library code
├── web/                   # Frontend React application
│   ├── src/              # React source code
│   └── public/           # Static assets
├── test/                  # Additional test files
├── Dockerfile            # Main Dockerfile
├── docker-compose.yml    # Docker compose configuration
└── go.mod                # Go module file
```

## Key Files

- [go.mod](mdc:go.mod) - Go module definition
- [Dockerfile](mdc:Dockerfile) - Main application container
- [docker-compose.yml](mdc:docker-compose.yml) - Local development environment
- [web/src/App.tsx](mdc:web/src/App.tsx) - Main React application
